---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy" 
  description="Privacy policy for OncologyIT.com">
  
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Last updated: March 2026</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        OncologyIT.com is a public directory website that does not require user accounts 
        or collect personal information for general browsing. We may collect:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Anonymous usage data:</strong> Basic analytics about page views and visitor behavior</li>
        <li><strong>Technical information:</strong> Browser type, device type, and general location (country/region level)</li>
        <li><strong>Referral data:</strong> How visitors found our website</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>
        We use collected information to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Improve website performance and user experience</li>
        <li>Understand which content is most valuable to visitors</li>
        <li>Identify technical issues that need to be addressed</li>
        <li>Make decisions about future content and features</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        We may use third-party services that collect information:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Analytics services:</strong> To understand website usage patterns</li>
        <li><strong>Hosting providers:</strong> To serve website content</li>
        <li><strong>Content delivery networks:</strong> To improve website performance</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These services have their own privacy policies governing how they handle data.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>External Links</h2>
      <p>
        Our website contains links to external vendor websites. We are not responsible for 
        the privacy practices or content of these external sites. We encourage you to review 
        the privacy policies of any website you visit through our links.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We implement reasonable security measures to protect against unauthorized access 
        to or unauthorized alteration, disclosure, or destruction of data. However, no 
        internet transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee the security 
        of information transmitted to or from our website.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify users of 
        any material changes by posting the new privacy policy on this page and updating 
        the "Last updated" date.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this privacy policy, please contact us through 
        our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <style>
    .page-header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
    
    .page-header h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      color: var(--primary);
    }
    
    .subtitle {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--text-light);
    }
    
    .content {
      background: white;
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 3rem;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    }
    
    section {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
    
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      color: var(--text);
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    
    p {
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--text);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    
    ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    
    li {
      padding: 0.5rem 0;
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      position: relative;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    
    li:before {
      content: "•";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--primary);
    }
    
    strong {
      color: var(--text);
    }
    
    a {
      color: var(--primary);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
    
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .page-header h1 {
        font-size: 2rem;
      }
      
      .content {
        padding: 2rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>